trend_summary: Across the series the area stays medium-density suburbia. Incremental infill raises built coverage along the central corridor, several large white-roofed commercial blocks replace older fabric, and a small subdivision fills vacant land near the river. Meanwhile roadside greening and parkland expansion lift tree canopy, giving a slightly more vegetated appearance overall.
notable_changes: Expansion of white-roofed commercial/industrial buildings along the main east-west artery.
Creation of a cul-de-sac housing pocket near the southwest river bend.
Widening and realignment of the northern expressway and its interchange.
Noticeable increase in residential street tree canopy and riverside park vegetation.
Demolition of scattered warehouses replaced by larger retail complexes toward the centre.
